title: Tech and Financial Stocks Drive Modest Gains on Wall Street Amid AI Concerns
description: U.S. stocks saw modest gains as technology shares rebounded and financial stocks provided support. Artificial intelligence concerns had previously triggered selloffs. title: Fed must dig deep on AI impact to make right rate calls ahead, Daly says
description: The Federal Reserve must dig deep on the data to assess whether artificial intelligence is boosting productivity growth and enabling faster economic growth without igniting inflation or requiring the Fed to tap the brakes with tighter policy, San Francisco Fed President Mary Daly said on Tuesday.

title: India's 'AI for All' plan can push development: World Bank VP Sangbu Kim
description: Artificial intelligence governance needs both global rules and national regulations. India's 'AI for All' approach holds significant development potential. Developing nations can leapfrog by focusing on practical AI solutions. AI can augment jobs in South Asia rather than solely replacing them. India's digital infrastructure supports large-scale AI integration.
